# Enterprise Frontend Foundation — Mental Model & Rules

## The One Rule
**Every new page follows the same pattern. No exceptions.**

```
Page = ApiStateWrapper + AppTable (or AppForm) + Modal(AppForm) + useApiMutation
```

You never:
- Write raw `<Table>` from antd
- Write raw `<Form>` from antd
- Handle loading/error/empty states manually
- Import from `antd` directly in feature code

---

## File Map

```
shared/
  types/
    api-error.types.ts       ← AppError shape (single source of truth)
  utils/
    normalizeError.ts        ← Converts ANY error → AppError
  components/
    ApiState/
      ApiStateWrapper.tsx    ← loading skeleton | error+retry | empty state | children
    AppTable/
      AppTable.tsx           ← col.* builder + pagination + actions
    AppForm/
      AppForm.tsx            ← schema-driven form + server error mapping
  hooks/
    useTableState.ts         ← URL-synced pagination/sort/filter state
    useApiMutation.ts        ← mutation wrapper + toast + normalised error
```

---

## Adding a New Feature (checklist)

### 1. Create the API slice (copy userApi.ts)
```ts
// features/orders/services/orderApi.ts
export const orderApi = createApi({
  reducerPath: "orderApi",
  baseQuery: baseQueryWithReauth,   // ← always this, never raw fetchBaseQuery
  tagTypes: ["Order"],
  endpoints: (builder) => ({
    getOrders: builder.query<PaginatedResponse<Order>, GetOrdersArgs>({ ... }),
    createOrder: builder.mutation<Order, CreateOrderDto>({ ... }),
  }),
});
```

### 2. Add to rootReducer
```ts
[orderApi.reducerPath]: orderApi.reducer,
```

### 3. Add to store middleware
```ts
middleware: (gm) => gm().concat(authApi.middleware, orderApi.middleware, ...),
```

### 4. Build the page (copy UserListPage.tsx pattern)

---

## Status Badge Convention
Always define status maps at the feature level:
```ts
const ORDER_STATUS_MAP = {
  pending:   { label: "Pending",   color: "warning"  },
  confirmed: { label: "Confirmed", color: "processing"},
  shipped:   { label: "Shipped",   color: "success"  },
  cancelled: { label: "Cancelled", color: "error"    },
} as const;
```
Then use: `col.status("status", "Status", { map: ORDER_STATUS_MAP })`

---

## Form Schema Convention
Define field schemas as **const arrays at module level**, not inside components:
```ts
// ✅ Good — defined once, reusable
const ORDER_FORM_FIELDS: FormFieldDef[] = [ ... ];

// ❌ Bad — recreated on every render
const MyForm = () => {
  const fields = [ ... ]; // inside component
};
```

---

## Error Handling Decision Tree

```
API call fails
    │
    ├── 401 → baseQueryWithReauth handles silently (refresh + retry)
    │
    ├── 400/422 → normalizeError gives fieldErrors → AppForm maps them
    │
    ├── 403 → ApiStateWrapper shows "No permission" state
    │
    ├── 404 → ApiStateWrapper shows "Not found" state
    │
    ├── 5xx → ApiStateWrapper shows error + Retry button
    │
    └── Network → ApiStateWrapper shows "No internet" + Retry button
```

---

## Pagination Contract
Your RTK Query endpoints should return:
```ts
{
  items: T[];
  total: number;
  page: number;
  pageSize: number;
}
```
If your backend returns differently, adapt `transformResponse` **only in that endpoint's file**.
The rest of the system never changes.

---

## Column Builder Reference
```ts
col.text("fieldName", "Column Title", { sortable: true })
col.status("status", "Status", { map: STATUS_MAP })
col.date("createdAt", "Created")
col.dateTime("updatedAt", "Last updated", { sortable: true })
col.money("amount", "Amount", { currency: "INR" })
col.bool("isActive", "Active", { trueLabel: "Yes", falseLabel: "No" })
col.actions([
  { label: "Edit", onClick: openEdit },
  { label: "Delete", danger: true, confirm: true, onClick: doDelete },
])
```

---

## CSS Rules
- Never write inline colors — use `var(--color-text-primary)`, `var(--color-background-secondary)` etc.
- Never import from `antd` in feature code — always via `useUILibrary()`
- Tailwind for spacing/layout only (`p-6`, `flex`, `gap-4`)
- Status badges: use the StatusMap system, never ad-hoc inline styles per component

---

## What Changes When Backend Changes
| Backend changes | What you touch |
|---|---|
| Field name renames | `transformResponse` in that feature's api.ts |
| New status values | That feature's STATUS_MAP const |
| New field validation rules | FormFieldDef `rules` array |
| Pagination shape changes | `transformResponse` in that feature's api.ts |
| Auth flow changes | `baseQueryWithReauth.ts` only |
| Error message format | `normalizeError.ts` extractFieldErrors section |
| Add new field type | `AppForm.tsx` FieldRenderer switch case |